President Trump delivered remarks at Naval Station Norfolk, expressing gratitude to the dedicated service members who will soon be on the frontlines in the fight against COVID-19. The Navy Hospital Ship USNS Comfort will be deployed to New York City to provide care for non-infected patients who require urgent medical attention, freeing up hospital beds for COVID-19 patients. The ship is equipped with 12 operating rooms, 1,000 hospital beds, and various medical facilities. Trump also mentioned the USNS Mercy, which arrived in Los Angeles ahead of schedule to perform a similar mission. The President discussed efforts to ramp up ventilator production, mentioning that the US may be able to help other countries with ventilator shortages in the future. He also highlighted the mobilization of American companies to produce essential medical equipment and the passage of the economic relief package, which includes job retention loans for small businesses and direct cash payments to American citizens. Trump praised the resilience and strength of the American people and expressed confidence in the nation's ability to overcome the challenges posed by the pandemic.